{"type":"step-attempt","step":"spec-review","sessionId":"37808c35-43fe-4b18-935b-888c240ad456","outcome":{"verdict":"needs-fix","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/auth-login-ui/spec-review-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":false,"findings":[{"severity":"high","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/auth-login-ui/tasks.md","title":"Open redirect via unvalidated `next` parameter in loginAction","rationale":"tasks.md T-07 instructs the implementer to call `redirect(next || '/')` where `next` comes from `formData.get('next')` — a client-controlled value. An attacker can craft `/login?next=https://evil.com`, which the middleware embeds into the login form as a hidden field. On successful login the action blindly redirects to the attacker-controlled URL, enabling phishing post-authentication (CWE-601, OWASP A01). The middleware's own redirect is safe because it uses `request.nextUrl.pathname` (server-controlled), but the form field is user-tamperable.","line":117},{"severity":"medium","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/auth-login-ui/design.md","title":"Timing-based user enumeration risk not tracked for follow-up","rationale":"`authenticate()` short-circuits and returns null immediately when an email is not found, skipping the slow password-hash verification. The measurable timing difference reveals whether an email address exists. The spec correctly marks this out-of-scope, but design.md Risks does not record a follow-up action for a future slice, leaving the gap undocumented.","line":96},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/auth-login-ui/tasks.md","title":"Email display in nav: implementation path unspecified","rationale":"`SessionPayload` contains only `{ userId, role, exp }` — no email field. Request requirement 7 says to display 'ユーザー識別（email）' in the nav, and tasks.md T-09 does not specify how to obtain the email (options: `resolveAuthConfig(process.env).adminEmail` vs. `getUserRepository()` lookup by userId). The ambiguity leaves the implementer to guess. Already flagged as LOW in the request-review.","line":155}],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"specrunner/changes/auth-login-ui/spec.md","title":"spec.md format is fully compliant with rules.md spec authority","rationale":"All Requirements use `### Requirement:` headers with at least one `#### Scenario:`, include `SHALL` normative keywords, and follow Given/When/Then form."},{"severity":"low","file":"specrunner/changes/auth-login-ui/design.md","title":"D7 two-layer path filtering (config.matcher + isPublicPath) is coherent","rationale":"config.matcher excludes Next.js internals at the framework level for performance; isPublicPath handles app-level public paths as a pure function. The separation is clean and testable."}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-06-18T01:48:16.814Z","endedAt":"2026-06-18T01:52:21.790Z"}
